Solution: Let's say that the probability of receiving a dot given that a dot is sent is $P(d|d)$ and the probability of receiving a dash given that a dash is sent is $P(d|d)$. Then, we have

\begin{align} P(d|d) &= \frac{1}{7} \\ P(d|d) &= \frac{1}{7} \\ \end{align}

Now, we can calculate the probability of receiving a dot given that a dot or a dash is sent:

\begin{align} P(d|d \text{ or } d) &= \frac{P(d \text{ and } d)}{P(d \text{ or } d)} \\ &= \frac{P(d) \times P(d)}{P(d) \times P(d) + P(d) \times P(d)} \\ &= \frac{1}{3} \\ \end{align}

Finally, we can calculate the probability of receiving a dot given that a dot was sent:

\begin{align} P(d|d) &= \frac{P(d \text{ and } d)}{P(d)} \\ &= \frac{P(d) \times P(d)}{P(d) \times P(d) + P(d) \times P(d)} \\ &= \frac{1}{3} \\ \end{align}
